The best way of self injection is to use the right size needland choose the correct spot. For Streptomycin, usually given intrmuscularly, use a thin needle (23/24 guage) and select a spot othe upper, outer thigh (no major nerves or blood vessels there).Clean the area with antiseptic before injection, and after. Maksure to inject deeply (a different kind of pain is felt when thneedle enters the muscle - contrasted to the 'prick' when itpierces the skin)PS: Try to go to a doctor. Self-treatment and self-injection shoulbe avoided as far as possible